OL,3,C'They were the loudest audience':
OL,4,CBarry Manilow on his British 'Fanilows'
OL,6,F"I didn't really know what I was doing
OL,7,Fback then, I had no intention of being
OL,8,Fa singer or a performer. I thought I
OL,9,Fstunk, but they didn't, they in their
OL,10,Fown way kept saying: keep going. So I
OL,11,Fgive them all the credits for my
OL,12,Fsuccess."
OL,14,FHe's calling time on touring, singing
OL,15,Foff from the UK with a 14-date run at
OL,16,Fthe London Palladium, where it all
OL,17,Fstarted nearly 50 yeas ago.
OL,19,F"I'm done with touring," he tells me
OL,20,Fwith an element of relief in his tone.
